Illinois Regional Bancorp saidit is evaluating whether to affiliate with a larger bankholding company or continue to remain independent.    The 500 mln dlr-asset bank holding company said that inview of recent investor interest in suburban Chicago banks, itretained Merrill Lynch Capital markets to advise it on itsalternatives.    Last year, Illinois Regional had discussions withMilwaukee-based Marine Corp &lt;MCRP> but no agreement wasreached, a company spokesman said. Reuter&#3;